<event name="HARMONY_LINK_FIGHTENGI">
	<text>An Engi ship is resting nearby the Harmony Link. It's an elite, but they aren't attacking just yet.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_ENGI_ELITE_FIGHT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attack them!</text>
		<event>
			<text>As you approach, suddenly the Engi ship activates and its drones come online. "Multiverse-Drive equipped vessel approaching. Threat to Harmony Link: activating defensive protocols."</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ENGI_FIGHT"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Request supplies.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Refusal. Task: protecting Harmony link. Do not interfere." Looks like you won't be getting anything out of them.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>If they won't give us supplies, we'll take them!</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Multiverse-Drive equipped vessel approaching. Threat to Harmony Link: activating defensive protocols."</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ENGI_FIGHT"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Leave.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_HARMONY">
		<text>(Engi Crew) Request supplies.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Harmony unit detected. Protocol requires aid to be given."</text>
			<autoReward level="MED">droneparts_only</autoReward>
			<damage amount="-3"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the Engi.</text>
		<event>
			<text>If they're no threat to you, then you'll be no threat to them.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="HARMONY_LINK_FIGHTMANTIS">
    <text>A Suzerain ship is waiting near the beacon, likely hunting for Engi. "Federation, we recommend staying away, unless want to become next prey..."</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_SUZERAIN_FIGHT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attack them!</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Fine. If have death wish, then let me be one to grant it!"</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ask if they have slaves to offer.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Hmmm. Hoping for trade? Well... maybe. Made successful hunt previously, supposed go to Hive though, so prices steep."</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Buy a regular Engi.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Good, good. Now leave, there killing to be done."</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="engi"/>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="scrap" min="-45" max="-50"/>
					</item_modify>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Buy an Engi Defender.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Good, good. Now leave, there killing to be done."</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="engi_defender"/>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="scrap" min="-125" max="-135"/>
					</item_modify>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Nevermind.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the Mantis.</text>
		<event>
			<text>If they're no threat to you, then you'll be no threat to them.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<ship name="SHIP_ANCIENT_AUTOSTART" auto_blueprint="LIST_SHIPS_ANCIENT_AUTO">
	<destroyed load="HARMONY_LINK_ANCIENT_WIN"/>
	<surrender min="3" max="4">
		<text>Suddenly, the ship sends a transmission, whose language is indiscernible. Your translator struggles, turning out nonsense like "Turkey alpha on the blue yesterday." The transmission stops, and immediately after your systems go haywire! The ship has activated some kind of bizarre combat augment!</text>
		<status type="limit" target="player" system="sensors" amount="0"/>
		<status type="limit" target="player" system="doors" amount="0"/>
		<status type="divide" target="player" system="shields" amount="2"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event>
				<text>To make matters worse, it appears the ship's remaining systems have come online!</text>
				<status type="clear" target="enemy" system="drones" amount="100"/>
				<status type="clear" target="enemy" system="hacking" amount="100"/>
				<status type="clear" target="enemy" system="mind" amount="100"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event>
						<status type="clear" target="enemy" system="cloaking" amount="100"/>
					</event>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</surrender>
</ship>
<event name="HARMONY_LINK_ANCIENT">
	<text>Orbiting around the Link is the wreckage of several massive structures... or are they ships? Composed of gigantic cubical segments, the ships are larger than any vessel you've ever seen, but they've been completely decimated. A strangely designed, but non-cubical, automaton rests silently by the wreckage. You aren't sure if moving closer will awaken it.</text>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="false" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_ANCIENT_WRECKAGE</customFleet>
	<variable name="loc_foundancient" op="set" val="1"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_ANCIENT_AUTOSTART" hostile="false"/>
	<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="cloaking" amount="0"/>
	<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="hacking" amount="0"/>
	<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="mind" amount="0"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Destroy the ship first, just in case.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You approach the vessel, and it activates automatically, as you expected. Prepare for combat! It seems like the ship isn't using all of its systems... let's hope it stays that way!</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="drones" amount="0"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attempt to salvage without alerting the ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You attempt to scrap the furthest regions of the wreckage, but not long after you see the Auto-ship approaching, awakened by your presence! It gets a shot off, damaging your hull, and you quickly pull the crew back into the ship with what you've gathered so far. It seems like the ship isn't using all of its systems... let's hope it stays that way!</text>
			<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
			<damage amount="3"/>
			<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="drones" amount="0"/>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the crash site.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You warily distance yourself from the vessel. You can almost make out the lights flickering on the vessel and the slightest movement to observe your ship, as if it were watching...</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="HARMONY_LINK_ANCIENT_WIN">
	<text>The foreign Auto-ship has been eliminated. You find a large helping of scrap in the wreckage.</text>
	<variable name="loc_got_corpse" op="set" val="1"/>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	<status type="clear" target="player" system="sensors" amount="100"/>
	<status type="clear" target="player" system="doors" amount="100"/>
	<status type="clear" target="player" system="shields" amount="100"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Without the Auto-ship to disturb you, you scout out the remaining wreckage. It appears most of the hull material is unrecognized by your database, and it's too strong to easily be stripped for scrap. Whoever made these ships must have been highly advanced, or from a completely different galaxy...</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>Inside one of the larger cruisers you're surprised to find what appears to be a robot of some sorts, entirely cubical in craft just like the ships. The room around it has been partially dissolved and strange looking Lanius corpses are scattered around. You bring back the robot to the ship out of curiosity, but without any obvious way to activate it, it'll have to remain in the back corners of the storage bay for now. Along with it, you find some strange coords that you mark on your map.</text>
					<quest event="AUGMENTED_DISCOVERY"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

