	</choice>
</event>

<event name="ENGI_VIRUS" unique="true">
	<text>The Engi are awaiting you at the beacon, with their weapons online! They explain a computer virus that is wanted for hostile acts against the Engi (multiple counts of binary scrambling, nano-dissolution, and variable interference) is aboard your vessel.</text>
	<choice>
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>They insist they must destroy your ship to prevent the virus from escaping!</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Hold on! Let us try to purge the system code!</text>
				<event>
					<text>Wiping your Engine core and shields proves useless... eventually you trap the virus in the weapons systems to purge it, but before you do, the Engi grow restless and attack!</text>
					<status type="divide" target="player" system="shields" amount="2"/>
					<status type="divide" target="player" system="engines" amount="2"/>
					<ship load="SHIP_ENGI_VIRUS" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Attack the Engi vessel!</text>
				<event>
					<text>The Engi be damned, no one threatens your ship. You prepare for a fight!</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_ENGI_VIRUS" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ENGI_FIGHT"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="hacking" lvl="1" max_group="0" hidden="true">
				<text>(Hacking System) Isolate and quarantine the virus.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It takes some time, and the virus is slippery, but you eventually confine it to a useless sub-system prison where it frantically begins calculating insults at you. You eject the system from the ship and then silence the little binary criminal with your weapons.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>The Engi thank you for deleting the virus, and jump away. They offer am augmentation as a reward.</text>
							<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
							<augment name="RANDOM"/>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="hacking" lvl="2" max_group="0" hidden="true">
				<text>(Improved Hacking) Reprogram the virus.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You proceed to interface with the virus and optimize its repair and benevolence routines.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>After a few minutes, the virus "sees the light" and integrates itself in a positive manner with the computer society on your ship, repairing your hull and attempting to optimize your reactor.</text>
							<damage amount="-15"/>
							<upgrade amount="1" system="reactor"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event>
									<text>The Engi thank you for deleting the virus, and jump away. They offer an augmentation as a reward.</text>
									<augment name="RANDOM"/>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="hacking" lvl="3" max_group="0" hidden="true">
				<text>(Advanced Hacking) Reprogram the virus.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You proceed to interface with the virus and optimize its repair and benevolence routines.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>After a few minutes, the virus "sees the light" and integrates itself in a positive manner with the computer society on your ship, repairing your hull and attempting to optimize your reactor.</text>
							<damage amount="-30"/>
							<upgrade amount="1" system="reactor"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event>
									<text>The Engi thank you for deleting the virus, and jump away. They offer an augmentation as a reward.</text>
									<augment name="RANDOM"/>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="ANTI_VIRUS">
				<text>(Anti-Virus) Purge the virus.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Your Anti-Virus makes quick work, finding the hostile code and erasing it from existence.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>The Engi thank you for deleting the virus, and jump away. They offer an augmentation as a reward.</text>
							<augment name="RANDOM"/>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="LIST_CREW_LANIUS" hidden="true">
				<text>(Lanius Crew) Your Lanius crewmember gestures frantically.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Oddly enough, the Lanius seems aware of which computer the virus is present in, and proceeds to... digest the terminal. There is a burst of O2, and the Engi ship powers down its weapons, no longer sensing the virus on board. The Engi send some parts over to repair your damaged computer, along with an augmentation as a reward for terminating the virus.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">scrap_only</autoReward>
					<augment name="RANDOM"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="engi" hidden="true">
				<text>(Engi Crew) Have your Engi crewmember negotiate with the Engi ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>As the Engi attempts to contact the vessel and negotiate, your Engi crewmember suddenly dissolves into nanites - the virus has murdered again! Detecting activity on board your ship, the Engi vessel opens fire!</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_ENGI_VIRUS_ALT" hostile="true"/>
					<removeCrew class="engi">
						<clone>false</clone>
						<text>The virus appears to have disrupted your clone bay's capability to revive the lost crewmember!</text>
					</removeCrew>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="engi_defender" hidden="true">
				<text>(Engi Defender) Have your Defender crewmember negotiate with the Engi ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>As the Engi attempts to contact the vessel and negotiate, your Defender crewmember suddenly collapses, struggling - the virus must have infected them! However, your Defender gets up not long after. "Threat neutralized. Deleted code: 2 lines." This seems good enough for the Engi ship, and they reward you for deleting the virus.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">scrap_only</autoReward>
					<augment name="RANDOM"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="LIST_CREW_COGNITIVE_ALL" hidden="true">
				<text>(Cognitive Crew) Have your Cognitive negotiate with the virus.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You explain to the Engi that you might have a solution, then wait for your Cognitive to do its job. Not too long after, the Cognitive comes back online. "Negotiation attempts have failed, resorted to alternative methods. I instead convinced the virus that life is pointless. Once it had adopted the same nihilistic philosophies that plague my databanks, it decided to end its life rather than continue to suffer." Satisfied, the Engi ship rewards you for deleting the virus.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">scrap_only</autoReward>
					<augment name="RANDOM"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
